{
  "message": "licensing: adopt MIT + OpenAI/Anthropic rider metadata across workspace\n\nSummary:\n- Replaces repository LICENSE text with the MIT license plus OpenAI/Anthropic rider.\n- Switches workspace package metadata from SPDX \"MIT\" to explicit LICENSE file reference.\n- Migrates crate manifests to inherited license-file metadata so published package metadata points to the ridered LICENSE.\n\nDetails:\n- Updated root workspace metadata in Cargo.toml to use `license-file = \"LICENSE\"`.\n- Updated crate manifests (except ffs-repair, committed with the self-healing command update) from `license.workspace = true` to `license-file.workspace = true`.\n- Keeps repository/source metadata unchanged while making licensing declaration explicit and consistent with the repository license text.\n\nRationale:\n- The rider is a condition of use and must be reflected consistently in package metadata, not only in the root LICENSE file.\n- Using license-file avoids incorrectly advertising plain MIT SPDX semantics once the rider is present.",
  "files": [
    {
      "sha": "984b708c081513b17bdbb2254ef7c6f2bae36a9a",
      "filename": "Cargo.toml",
      "status": "modified",
      "additions": 1,
      "deletions": 1,
      "changes": 2,
      "blob_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/blob/9cb3ba58f90cb867be567db80180282d229a1217/Cargo.toml",
      "raw_url": "https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/raw/9cb3ba58f90cb867be567db80180282d229a1217/Cargo.toml",
      "contents_url": "https://api.github.com/repos/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs/contents/Cargo.toml?ref=9cb3ba58f90cb867be567db80180282d229a1217",
      "patch": "@@ -27,7 +27,7 @@ members = [\n \n [workspace.package]\n edition = \"2024\"\n-license = \"MIT\"\n+license-file = \"LICENSE\"\n repository = \"https://github.com/Dicklesworthstone/frankenfs\"\n rust-version = \"1.85\"\n "
    },
